### Health check
GET http://localhost:3000/

###

### Get all todos (empty or list)
GET http://localhost:3000/todos

###

### Create a new todo (valid)
POST http://localhost:3000/todos
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learn Go",
  "completed": false
}

###

### Create todo without completed (defaults to false)
POST http://localhost:3000/todos
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Write API"
}

###

### Create todo with missing title (should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/todos
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "completed": true
}

###

### Create todo with invalid JSON (should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/todos
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Broken JSON",

###

### Get todo by valid ID
GET http://localhost:3000/todos/1

###

### Get todo with invalid ID (string)
GET http://localhost:3000/todos/abc

###

### Get todo that doesn't exist
GET http://localhost:3000/todos/9999

###

### Update ONLY title (Completed = nil)
PUT http://localhost:3000/todos/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Title Only"
}

###

### Update ONLY completed (Title = nil)
PUT http://localhost:3000/todos/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "completed": true
}

###

### Update BOTH fields
PUT http://localhost:3000/todos/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Fully Updated",
  "completed": true
}

###

### Update with empty body (should fail)
PUT http://localhost:3000/todos/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
}

###

### Update with invalid ID
PUT http://localhost:3000/todos/abc
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Fail case"
}

###

### Update non-existing todo
PUT http://localhost:3000/todos/9999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Does not exist"
}

###
